[2026-03-16T17:14:26Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TqLHTKEsKF9ceU32q4Dtbq","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n## Comprehensive Analysis: Cloche Loop, Configuration, Failure Tracking, and Stop Mechanisms\n\nBased on my thorough search of the codebase, here's a complete understanding of how the cloche loop works:\n\n---\n\n### 1. THE CLOCHE LOOP IMPLEMENTATION\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\nThe cloche loop is a continuous orchestration engine that keeps up to `MaxConcurrent` host workflow runs active at all times when work is available.\n\n#### Loop Architecture\n\nThe `Loop` struct (lines 68-88) manages:\n- **Configuration** (`LoopConfig`): Defines project directory, max concurrent runs, stagger delays, dedup windows, and error handling\n- **Work Discovery**: Via `ListTasksFunc` (phase mode) or `TaskAssigner` (legacy mode)\n- **Execution**: Via `MainFunc` and optional `FinalizeFunc` (phase mode) or single `RunFunc` (legacy mode)\n- **State Management**: Run store persistence, task deduplication, halt states\n- **Synchronization**: Channels (`stopCh`, `resumeCh`), mutexes for thread-safe state\n\n**Key Constants:**\n```\ndefaultMaxConcurrent = 1\ndefaultDedupTimeout  = 5 * time.Minute\nidlePollInterval     = 2 * time.Minute\ncapacityPollInterval = 30 * time.Second\n```\n\n#### Two Execution Modes\n\n**1. Three-Phase Mode** (`runPhased()`, lines 222-334):\n- Discovers open tasks via `list-tasks` workflow\n- Launches `main` workflow for each unassigned task (up to `MaxConcurrent`)\n- Runs optional `finalize` workflow after main completes (on both success and failure)\n- Combines outcomes: finalize state is \"worse of\" main and finalize results\n\n**2. Legacy Mode** (`runLegacy()`, lines 417-513):\n- Single `RunFunc` per invocation\n- Optional task assignment via `ScriptTaskAssigner` (shell command)\n- Simpler flow but less flexibility\n\n#### Core Loop Logic\n\nThe loop continuously:\n\n1. **Fills slots** (up to `MaxConcurrent`):\n   - Checks if loop is halted → stops picking new work\n   - Counts active host runs from store\n   - Picks next open task (with dedup window check)\n   - Stagger delays between consecutive launches\n\n2. **Launches goroutines** for each task:\n   - Main phase runs in background\n   - Finalize phase runs after main (if configured)\n   - Tracks run ID for each task\n   - Reports completion state back to main loop\n\n3. **Waits for completions**:\n   - Succeeded runs → immediately try to fill slots\n   - Failed/aborted runs → back off with `idlePollInterval` (2 min)\n   - Failed + `StopOnError` → **halt** the loop (stops picking new work)\n   - Idle (no work) → poll at `capacityPollInterval` (30 sec)\n\n#### Task Deduplication\n\nTasks are tracked in `dedup` map (task ID → assignment timestamp):\n- Window: `DedupTimeout` (default 5 minutes)\n- Prevents re-assignment of same task within window\n- Expired entries cleaned on each `pickTask()` call\n- Decouples from actual run completion (tasks can be retried after timeout)\n\n---\n\n### 2. PROJECT CONFIGURATION LOADING\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/config/config.go`\n\n#### Configuration Structure\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Active        bool                `toml:\"active\"`\n    Daemon        DaemonConfig        `toml:\"daemon\"`\n    Evolution     EvolutionConfig     `toml:\"evolution\"`\n    Orchestration OrchestrationConfig `toml:\"orchestration\"`\n}\n\ntype OrchestrationConfig struct {\n    Concurrency      int     `toml:\"concurrency\"`          // default: 1\n    StaggerSeconds   float64 `toml:\"stagger_seconds\"`      // delay between launches\n    ListTasksCommand string  `toml:\"list_tasks_command\"`   // legacy task assignment\n    DedupSeconds     float64 `toml:\"dedup_seconds\"`        // default: 300 (5 min)\n    StopOnError      bool    `toml:\"stop_on_error\"`        // halt on unrecovered error\n}\n```\n\n#### Loading Hierarchy\n\n**Per-Project Config:**\n- Path: `<projectDir>/.cloche/config.toml`\n- Function: `config.Load(projectDir)`\n- Returns defaults if file missing\n- Used by daemon to enable/configure loops\n\n**Global Daemon Config:**\n- Path: `~/.config/cloche/config` (or `/tmp/cloche/` if home unavailable)\n- Function: `config.LoadGlobal()` / `config.LoadGlobalFrom(path)`\n- Fallback for daemon-level settings\n\n**Example .cloche/config.toml:**\n```toml\nactive = true\n\n[orchestration]\nconcurrency = 5\nstagger_seconds = 5.0\ndedup_seconds = 300\n\n[evolution]\nenabled = false\ndebounce_seconds = 30\nmin_confidence = \"medium\"\nmax_prompt_bullets = 50\n```\n\n#### Configuration Priority (EnableLoop)\n\n1. Request parameters (RPC) override\n2. Project config (`.cloche/config.toml`)\n3. Hardcoded defaults in code\n\n---\n\n### 3. JOB FAILURE TRACKING & DETECTION\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` and `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n#### Run States\n\n```go\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n#### Failure Detection in Loop\n\n**Phase Mode (lines 316-325):**\n```go\ncase r := <-completions:\n    inFlight--\n    if r.state == domain.RunStateSucceeded {\n        continue  // Work done, fill slots immediately\n    }\n    // Run failed or aborted\n    if l.config.StopOnError {\n        l.halt(r.errMsg)  // HALT the loop\n    }\n    // Back off (2 min idle poll)\n    if !l.sleep(idlePollInterval) {\n        return\n    }\n```\n\n**Failure Propagation:**\n- Main phase fails/aborts → recorded in `RunResult.State`\n- Finalize phase fails → combined with main using `WorseState()`:\n  - `Succeeded` (0) < `Cancelled` (1) < `Failed` (2)\n- Overall task completion state = worse of (main, finalize)\n\n#### Error Recording\n\n**`Run.Fail(msg)`** (line 118-122):\n- Sets `State = RunStateFailed`\n- Records `CompletedAt = time.Now()`\n- Stores `ErrorMessage = msg`\n\n**Host Runner (runner.go lines 156-162):**\n```go\nif runErr != nil {\n    hostRun.Fail(runErr.Error())\n} else {\n    hostRun.Complete(result.State)\n}\n_ = s.Store.UpdateRun(ctx, hostRun)\n```\n\n#### Finding Failed Steps\n\n**`Run.FindFirstFailedStep()`** (lines 127-134):\n- Scans `StepExecutions` for first step with result \"fail\" or \"error\"\n- Used during resume to know which step to restart from\n\n#### Task Status Aggregation\n\n**`TaskAggregateStatus(runs)`** (lines 165-206):\n- Active statuses (running, pending) outweigh terminal ones\n- Among terminal: prefer host runs (full attempt) over container runs\n- If no host runs: use most-recently-started run\n\n---\n\n### 4. LOOP STOPPING & STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` and `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go`\n\n#### Starting the Loop\n\n**EnableLoop RPC** (lines 1036-1092):\n1. Loads project config from `.cloche/config.toml`\n2. Verifies host workflows exist\n3. Creates loop config from settings + RPC overrides\n4. Selects mode:\n   - **Phase mode** if \"list-tasks\" workflow exists\n   - **Legacy mode** otherwise\n5. Calls `loop.Start()` (spawns background goroutine)\n\n#### Stopping the Loop\n\n**Stop() Method** (lines 151-160):\n```go\nfunc (l *Loop) Stop() {\n    l.mu.Lock()\n    defer l.mu.Unlock()\n    if !l.running {\n        return\n    }\n    l.running = false\n    close(l.stopCh)  // Signals main loop to exit\n    log.Printf(\"orchestration loop: stopped for %s\", l.config.ProjectDir)\n}\n```\n\n**DisableLoop RPC** (lines 1239-1254):\n```go\nif loop, ok := s.loops[projectDir]; ok {\n    loop.Stop()              // Stops picking new work\n    delete(s.loops, projectDir)  // Unregisters\n}\n```\n\n**Active Runs:** Continue to completion after Stop() is called.\n\n#### Halting (Error Stop)\n\nWhen `StopOnError = true` and a run fails:\n\n**halt() Internal** (lines 195-201):\n```go\nfunc (l *Loop) halt(errMsg string) {\n    l.haltedMu.Lock()\n    defer l.haltedMu.Unlock()\n    l.halted = true\n    l.haltError = errMsg\n    log.Printf(\"orchestration loop: halted for %s (stop_on_error): %s\",\n        l.config.ProjectDir, errMsg)\n}\n```\n\n**Halted() Query** (lines 172-176):\n- Returns `(bool, string)` — halted status and error message\n- Loop checks `isHalted()` before picking new work (line 242)\n\n#### Resuming from Halt\n\n**Resume() Method** (lines 179-192):\n```go\nfunc (l *Loop) Resume() {\n    l.haltedMu.Lock()\n    defer l.haltedMu.Unlock()\n    if l.halted {\n        log.Printf(\"orchestration loop: resumed for %s (was halted: %s)\",\n            l.config.ProjectDir, l.haltError)\n        l.halted = false\n        l.haltError = \"\"\n        // Wake loop from sleep so it picks up work immediately\n        select {\n        case l.resumeCh <- struct{}{}:\n        default:\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**ResumeLoop RPC** (lines 1256-1272):\n- Looks up loop by project directory\n- Calls `loop.Resume()` to clear halted state\n- Returns error if no loop exists\n\n#### Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Shutdown RPC** (lines 1416-1440):\n```go\n// Stop all orchestration loops\ns.mu.Lock()\nfor _, loop := range s.loops {\n    loop.Stop()\n}\ns.loops = make(map[string]*host.Loop)\ns.mu.Unlock()\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. TASK ASSIGNMENT & WORKFLOW\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n\n#### Task Structure\n\n```go\ntype Task struct {\n    ID          string            `json:\"id\"`\n    Status      string            `json:\"status\"`    // \"open\", \"in-progress\", \"closed\"\n    Title       string            `json:\"title\"`\n    Description string            `json:\"description\"`\n    Metadata    map[string]string `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n}\n\nfunc (t Task) IsOpen() bool {\n    return t.Status == \"\" || TaskStatus(t.Status) == TaskStatusOpen\n}\n```\n\n#### Two Task Assignment Methods\n\n**1. Three-Phase (Recommended):**\n- `list-tasks` workflow outputs JSONL task objects\n- Parsed via `ParseTasksJSONL()` or `ReadListTasksOutput()`\n- Loop calls `ListTasksFunc` on each cycle\n- Only open tasks are considered\n\n**2. Legacy (Script-based):**\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner.ListTasks()` runs shell command\n- Command should output JSON array: `[{\"id\":\"task-1\", ...}, ...]`\n- Parsed to Task objects\n\n#### Task State Tracking\n\n**TaskAssignment** (lines 48-51):\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // Set after main completes\n}\n```\n\n**TaskStateEntry** (lines 54-59):\n```go\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool         // Within dedup window?\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string       // The run handling this task\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. INTEGRATION: DAEMON PERSPECTIVE\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n#### Startup Flow\n\n1. **Load global config** (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. **Initialize storage** (SQLite)\n3. **Sweep stale runs** (from previous crash)\n4. **Initialize container runtime** (Docker or local)\n5. **Auto-run active projects** (line 118):\n   - Scans all known projects\n   - Loads each project's `.cloche/config.toml`\n   - If `active = true`, spawns one-off host workflow run\n6. **Start gRPC server** (listening on socket/TCP)\n\n#### Project Info Reporting\n\n**GetProjectInfo RPC** (lines 1274-1388):\n- Resolves project by directory or name\n- Loads config\n- Checks loop state: running, halted, or stopped\n- Reports loop status: `LoopRunning`, `ErrorHalted`, `HaltError`\n- Lists active runs (pending/running)\n- Discovers workflows in `.cloche/` files\n- Returns configuration: concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error\n\n---\n\n### 7. KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Core loop orchestration (phased & legacy modes, dedup, halting) |\n| `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` | Configuration loading (project + global) |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run states, step tracking, failure detection, state aggregation |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow execution, result extraction, resumption |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task structures, assignment methods, JSONL parsing |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Loop lifecycle (Enable/Disable/Resume), project info, phase/legacy setup |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup, auto-run active projects, signal handling |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml` | Example project configuration |\n\n---\n\nThis architecture provides a robust, configurable orchestration system with built-in failure handling, task deduplication, and graceful shutdown semantics. The loop can operate autonomously with backoff strategies, or halt and await manual resume on errors depending on configuration."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a22fc0017b747bd0c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 65772\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 64945</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"77daf22e-aee8-40ec-9b79-2fa0d1f74d8f","uuid":"ffc27aca-6877-4e9f-b27e-0fecaed8ffc1","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand:\n1. How the \"cloche loop\" works - find the loop implementation\n2. How project configuration (cloche.toml) is loaded and structured\n3. How job failures are tracked/detected\n4. How the loop is stopped\n\nSearch for: loop-related code, project config structs, cloche.toml parsing, run status/failure tracking. Be very thorough - check cmd/, internal/domain/, internal/ports/, internal/adapters/, internal/host/. Look for files related to \"loop\", \"project\", \"config\", \"toml\".","agentId":"a22fc0017b747bd0c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the