L()` or `ReadListTasksOutput()`\n- Loop calls `ListTasksFunc` on each cycle\n- Only open tasks are considered\n\n**2. Legacy (Script-based):**\n- `ScriptTaskAssigner.ListTasks()` runs shell command\n- Command should output JSON array: `[{\"id\":\"task-1\", ...}, ...]`\n- Parsed to Task objects\n\n#### Task State Tracking\n\n**TaskAssignment** (lines 48-51):\n```go\ntype TaskAssignment struct {\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string  // Set after main completes\n}\n```\n\n**TaskStateEntry** (lines 54-59):\n```go\ntype TaskStateEntry struct {\n    Task       Task\n    Assigned   bool         // Within dedup window?\n    AssignedAt time.Time\n    RunID      string       // The run handling this task\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. INTEGRATION: DAEMON PERSPECTIVE\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go`\n\n#### Startup Flow\n\n1. **Load global config** (`~/.config/cloche/config`)\n2. **Initialize storage** (SQLite)\n3. **Sweep stale runs** (from previous crash)\n4. **Initialize container runtime** (Docker or local)\n5. **Auto-run active projects** (line 118):\n   - Scans all known projects\n   - Loads each project's `.cloche/config.toml`\n   - If `active = true`, spawns one-off host workflow run\n6. **Start gRPC server** (listening on socket/TCP)\n\n#### Project Info Reporting\n\n**GetProjectInfo RPC** (lines 1274-1388):\n- Resolves project by directory or name\n- Loads config\n- Checks loop state: running, halted, or stopped\n- Reports loop status: `LoopRunning`, `ErrorHalted`, `HaltError`\n- Lists active runs (pending/running)\n- Discovers workflows in `.cloche/` files\n- Returns configuration: concurrency, stagger, dedup, stop_on_error\n\n---\n\n### 7. KEY FILES SUMMARY\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/workspace/internal/host/loop.go` | Core loop orchestration (phased & legacy modes, dedup, halting) |\n| `/workspace/internal/config/config.go` | Configuration loading (project + global) |\n| `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` | Run states, step tracking, failure detection, state aggregation |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/runner.go` | Host workflow execution, result extraction, resumption |\n| `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` | Task structures, assignment methods, JSONL parsing |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | Loop lifecycle (Enable/Disable/Resume), project info, phase/legacy setup |\n| `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` | Daemon startup, auto-run active projects, signal handling |\n| `/workspace/.cloche/config.toml` | Example project configuration |\n\n---\n\nThis architecture provides a robust, configurable orchestration system with built-in failure handling, task deduplication, and graceful shutdown semantics. The loop can operate autonomously with backoff strategies, or halt and await manual resume on errors depending on configuration."}],"totalDurationMs":64945,"totalTokens":65772,"totalToolUseCount":31,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":526,"cache_read_input_tokens":61476,"output_tokens":3767,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":526},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
